2026-04-16 12:40:07 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['polarity / cabling configuration between power supply module and control (ambient sensor) module'] hypothesis_explanation='Measurements show that the control module internally passes input + to output + with low resistance, yet only ~0.36 V appears at the output while ~12 V is present at the input. The control electronics, sensor, relay and indicator circuits have all been verified or replaced with no effect. A recent test explicitly reports a POLARITY INVERSION between the power module and the control module: the lead designated as Control Input (+) is actually connected to the power module negative, and Control Input (−) is connected to the power module positive. With this reversed supply, the internal circuitry never operates in its intended region and the output remains at a low clamped level (~0.36 V) regardless of light or timing adjustments. Therefore the root cause is a configuration fault: the two cables between the power supply module and the control (ambient sensor) module are swapped. Correcting this wiring so that power module + goes to control input + and power module − goes to control input − will restore normal operation.'
