RESULT: The relay input (Control Input Cable (+)) is at ~11.99 V, and the relay output contact node (feeding the LED and Control Output Cable (+)) is at ~0.36 V. The ~12 V to ~0.36 V drop therefore occurs across the relay contact itself, not between the contact and the output connector.
