Instruction: With the control module disconnected from the load module, power the PSU and control module only. Measure the voltage between Control Output Cable (+) and Control Output Cable (−). Then, still powered, temporarily connect a high‑value resistor load (e.g., 10–47 kΩ) between these two output cables and observe whether the output remains near the same voltage or collapses. This tests whether any unexpected load external to the control module is pulling the relay output node down, versus the drop being intrinsic to the control module itself.
